# KUBECTL command line tools that allows you to interact with kubernetes

# KUBEADM tool for quickly and easily creating kubernetes cluster

# MINIKUBE similar to kubeadm, it allows to automatically to set up a local single-node kubernetes cluster.
           
#HELM provides templating and package management for k(s object.
      you can use it to manage your own templates (known as charts)
      you can also download and use shared templates
you can turn your k8s object or the applications you are running in you cluster into templates

#KOMPOSE helps you to translate Docker compose files into kubernetes objects, you can move your application to k8s easily with Kompose

#KUSTOMIZE configuration management tools for managing k8s object configurations
           it allown you to share and re-use templated configurations for k8s applications


